        <div class="ap-frw-step-pills">
          <div class="ap-frw-pill active" id="apFrwPill1"></div>
          <div class="ap-frw-pill" id="apFrwPill2"></div>
          <div class="ap-frw-pill" id="apFrwPill3"></div>
          <div class="ap-frw-pill" id="apFrwPill4"></div>
          <div class="ap-frw-pill" id="apFrwPill5"></div>
        </div>
        <p class="ap-frw-hero-label" id="apFrwStepLabel">Step 1 of 5</p>
        <h2 id="apFrwTitle">Fundraising for your team store</h2>
        <p id="apFrwSubtitle">The most seamless way to raise money — set up in under 5 minutes.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- STEP 1: How It Works + Agreement -->
      <div id="apFrwStep1" class="ap-frw-step-content">
        <div class="ap-frw-body">

          <div class="ap-frw-benefit-list">
            <div class="ap-frw-benefit-item">
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-icon" style="background:#f0fdf4">🏆</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-text">
                <strong>Every sale raises money — automatically</strong>
                <span>Add $1–$8 per item. The donation is built into your prices when you launch. Flip it on once and every product in your catalog raises money without any ongoing effort.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-benefit-item">
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-icon" style="background:#eff6ff">🏦</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-text">
                <strong>Funds go straight to the cause's bank</strong>
                <span>Stripe deposits fundraising dollars directly to the recipient's account after a 7-day hold. No invoices. No checks. No middleman — the money moves itself.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-benefit-item">
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-icon" style="background:#fefce8">📈</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-benefit-text">
                <strong>A live goal bar turns browsers into buyers</strong>
                <span>Show shoppers how close you are in real time. "We're at $340 of our $500 goal" creates urgency — people who were on the fence buy because they want to help push it over the line.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="ap-frw-legal-box">
            <span class="ap-frw-legal-intro">Read before you continue</span>
            <div class="ap-frw-legal-points">
              <div class="ap-frw-legal-point">Stella &amp; Sage Co. is a technology intermediary only — we do not hold, control, or distribute fundraising funds. All payments move directly through Stripe, Inc.</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-legal-point">As the Fundraiser Manager you are solely responsible for the lawful use of funds and compliance with all applicable laws, including charitable solicitation requirements.</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-legal-point">A $1 per-item processing fee is added on top of your set amount and disclosed to customers. Your cause always receives exactly the amount you set.</div>
              <div class="ap-frw-legal-point">This feature does not constitute a charitable donation and should not be represented as tax-deductible unless the receiving organization is a registered 501(c)(3).</div>
            </div>
            <label class="ap-frw-terms-label" for="apFrwTermsCheck">
              <input type="checkbox" id="apFrwTermsCheck" />
              <span><strong>I've read and agree to these terms.</strong> I understand Stella &amp; Sage Co. is not responsible for how funds are used after transfer, and I'm solely responsible for legal compliance.</span>
            </label>
          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="ap-frw-footer">
          <button class="ap-frw-next-btn" id="apFrwStep1Next">Got it — How does payment work? →</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STEP 2: About Stripe -->
      <div id="apFrwStep2" class="ap-frw-step-content" style="display:none;">
        <div class="ap-frw-body">

          <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro">
            <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro-header">
              <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro-icon">🏦</div>
              <div>
                <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro-title">What is Stripe?</div>
                <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro-sub">The payment infrastructure behind millions of businesses</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-stripe-intro-body">Stripe is the payment platform behind Apple Pay, Shopify, Lyft, and hundreds of thousands of small businesses. When you run a fundraiser here, Stripe handles every transfer from your store to the cause's bank — automatically, on a weekly schedule. You set it up once and walk away.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="ap-frw-info-card">
            <span class="ap-frw-info-card-label">What the recipient needs to open their account</span>
            <div class="ap-frw-info-row">
              <div class="ap-frw-info-dot"></div>
              <span><strong>Legal name</strong> — the individual or organization name as it appears on their bank account</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-info-row">
              <div class="ap-frw-info-dot"></div>
              <span><strong>Date of birth</strong> — for identity verification</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-info-row">
              <div class="ap-frw-info-dot"></div>
              <span><strong>Last 4 of SSN or full EIN</strong> — depends on payout volume</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-info-row">
              <div class="ap-frw-info-dot"></div>
              <span><strong>Bank account + routing number</strong> — where their deposits land</span>
            </div>
            <span class="ap-frw-info-card-note">Setup takes about 5 minutes — similar to any banking app. They only do it once. After that, Stripe handles every deposit automatically.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="ap-frw-info-callout">
            <strong>Who does this?</strong> Not you — the coach, booster club treasurer, or team parent who will receive the funds. They'll click "Connect with Stripe" on the next screen and walk through Stripe's guided setup. You never see or touch their banking information.
          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="ap-frw-footer">
          <button class="ap-frw-back-btn" id="apFrwStep2Back">← Back</button>
          <button class="ap-frw-next-btn" id="apFrwStep2Next">Connect the Cause →</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STEP 3: Stripe Connect -->
      <div id="apFrwStep3" class="ap-frw-step-content" style="display:none;">
        <div class="ap-frw-body">
          <div class="ap-frw-stripe-card">
            <div class="ap-frw-stripe-logo">🏦</div>
            <h3>Connect the Cause's Stripe Account</h3>
            <p>Have the recipient — the coach, booster club treasurer, or team parent — click below to set up their free Stripe Express account. It takes about 5 minutes. They enter their banking information directly with Stripe. You never see it.</p>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:#64748b;">Once connected, Stripe automatically deposits every fundraising dollar to their bank on a weekly basis. No action needed from either of you after setup.</p>
            <div id="apFrwStripeStatus">
              <button class="ap-frw-stripe-btn" id="apFrwStripeConnectBtn" type="button">
                Connect with Stripe
              </button>
              <p class="ap-frw-stripe-test-note" id="apFrwStripeTestNote">Test mode active — no real money moves. Switch to live after Stripe platform approval.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="apFrwStripeConnected" class="ap-frw-stripe-connected" style="display:none;">
              Connected — <span id="apFrwStripeAcctId"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ap-frw-highlight">
            <span class="ap-frw-highlight-icon">🔑</span>
            <div class="ap-frw-highlight-copy">
              <strong>This connects the recipient's bank, not yours.</strong> Once they complete setup, Stripe handles every deposit automatically — they never have to touch it again.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ap-frw-footer">
          <button class="ap-frw-back-btn" id="apFrwStep3Back">← Back</button>
          <button class="ap-frw-next-btn" id="apFrwStep3Next">Continue — Set Up Fundraiser →</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STEP 4: Fundraiser Details -->
      <div id="apFrwStep4" class="ap-frw-step-content" style="display:none;">
        <div class="ap-frw-body">

          <div class="ap-frw-field">
            <label class="ap-frw-label" for="apFrwCause">Cause Name</label>
            <input class="ap-frw-input" type="text" id="apFrwCause" placeholder="e.g. Westview Youth Baseball" maxlength="80" autocomplete="off" />
            <p class="ap-frw-helper">Shown on the storefront — customers see exactly who they're supporting.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="ap-frw-field">
            <label class="ap-frw-label">Fundraising Amount Per Item</label>
            <div class="ap-frw-amount-row">
              <button type="button" class="ap-frw-amt-btn" id="apFrwAmtDown" aria-label="Decrease">−</button>
              <div class="ap-frw-amt-display">$<span id="apFrwAmtDisplay">4</span></div>
              <button type="button" class="ap-frw-amt-btn" id="apFrwAmtUp" aria-label="Increase">+</button>
              <input type="hidden" id="apFrwAmount" value="4" />
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-calc-row">
              <span class="ap-frw-calc-label">$<span id="apFrwAmtA">4</span> to cause + $1 fee</span>
              <span class="ap-frw-calc-val">= $<span id="apFrwAmtB">5</span> per item</span>
            </div>
            <p class="ap-frw-helper">$1–$8 range. Your cause receives exactly the amount you set — the $1 fee is disclosed to customers.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="ap-frw-goal-row">
            <div class="ap-frw-field">
              <label class="ap-frw-label" for="apFrwGoal">Fundraising Goal</label>
              <div class="ap-frw-input-icon-wrap">
                <span class="ap-frw-input-pre">$</span>
                <input class="ap-frw-input ap-frw-input--icon-pre" type="number" id="apFrwGoal" min="1" step="1" placeholder="500" />
              </div>
              <p class="ap-frw-helper">Optional — shown publicly to drive urgency.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ap-frw-field">
              <label class="ap-frw-label" for="apFrwEndDate">End Date</label>
              <input class="ap-frw-input" type="date" id="apFrwEndDate" />
              <p class="ap-frw-helper">Optional. Max 1 year from today.</p>
